          "body": "Verse 22 contains a detail that is easily passed over: 'The LORD your God will clear away these nations before you little by little; you will not be able to put an end to them quickly, for the wild beasts would grow too numerous for you.' The gradual pace of conquest is not a concession to Israel's weakness — it is an expression of God's ecological and providential wisdom. A land cleared too quickly would be depopulated faster than Israel could fill it; the resulting vacuum would create a different kind of danger. This verse is a window into the God who governs not just by power but by wisdom — the same God who could instantaneously defeat every Canaanite nation chooses a pace calibrated to the realistic capacity of the people He is blessing. The lesson generalizes: when God's promised deliverance comes 'little by little,' it does not signal His inability; it signals His wisdom about what the next stage of our growth can sustainably bear."
